        <p>You can set each object to auto-size to fit text. To enable this setting, add an object to the frame. In the Object Properties window pane, expand the <span class="Emphasis">Object Layout</span> section and select <span class="Emphasis">Auto-size to fit text</span>. This setting will only be applied to the selected object.</p>
        <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #31b6f0;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">If Auto-size All Objects to Fit Text is set at the movie level, you will not have the option to set auto-size at the object level.</p>
